race.comment: BANGALOW ROAD (6) was an emphatic winner last time over 1450m at Kilmore with today's rider Rhys McLeod engaged. Is in solid form this time in work, scoring two times and placing on three occasions from seven starts. Should be in the finish. POETIC STORM (9) hasn't been far away lately, last time finishing fourth over 1200m at Ballarat, and gets some weight relief today. Brad Rawiller has registered two minor placings when on board. Well placed and should be in the finish. SACRED FORT (3) bounced back last start and got the job done by a nose when he produced a huge finish as favourite over 1200m at Echuca. Nicely placed to take this out. ON THE MOVE (13) resuming from a break. Ran fourth in a jump-out at Flemington. Opened last campaign with a third at Ballarat over 1400m. Can feature.
